response_parts.content:
{
  "response": [
    {
      "id": 0,
      "translated": "Yeah, I put those feelings into it and the tears just started flowing naturally."
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "translated": "There were parts where I got choked up and couldn't get the words out,"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "translated": "but that's what acting is all about. If I'm crying as Ena, then the character on screen is crying too."
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "translated": "Since I was crying as Ena, she was crying with me."
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "translated": "Usually, the dialogue moves forward with a button press, but they adjusted to my timing."
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "translated": "They didn't cut the recording and cherished every moment until the button was pressed. I'm so grateful."
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "translated": "I've received so many comments saying this was a great story. And it wasn't just about how my acting was,"
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "translated": "or how my voice sounded as Suzuki Minori."
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "translated": "Instead of focusing on me, everyone really took Ena's way of life to heart. Some felt encouraged to work hard too,"
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "translated": "and long-time fans were just so happy for her."
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "translated": "Even though her journey is just beginning, I'm so glad people felt so much for Ena."
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "translated": "I poured my absolute all into Ena for this, so I'm really happy with how it turned out."
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "translated": "That's right."
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "translated": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "translated": "Now, let's take a look at the illustrations."
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "translated": "By the way, I chose this one because it's the moment Ena finally sees a glimmer of hope after suffering for her art."
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "translated": "All right."
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "translated": "Let's spend about four minutes looking at the card illustrations together."
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "translated": "Before that, I have some comments from the illustration team about the costumes to share."
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "translated": "The theme of this story is Ena's struggle to get into art school, nearly giving up after falling short,"
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "translated": "but ultimately deciding not to quit."
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "translated": "The motif is an art apron over a school uniform,"
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "translated": "designed to capture Ena's look as a student preparing for entrance exams."
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "translated": "While she has other apron outfits, for this event, we gave Ena a patched-up apron."
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "translated": "This represents her persistence through repeated setbacks."
    },
    {
      "id": 25,
      "translated": "It's a unique arrangement for this specific story."
    },
    {
      "id": 26,
      "translated": "We kept strong uniform elements like the sailor collar and pleats,"
    },
    {
      "id": 27,
      "translated": "but modified the shape to give it more of a costume feel."
    },
    {
      "id": 28,
      "translated": "That's the design philosophy behind it."
    },
    {
      "id": 29,
      "translated": "And here is the illustration."
    },
    {
      "id": 30,
      "translated": "The pre-trained version... everyone gave such great feedback on this one."
    },
    {
      "id": 31,
      "translated": "She looks like she's having fun painting."
    },
    {
      "id": 32,
      "translated": "Her hands are all messy."
    },
    {
      "id": 33,
      "translated": "It's so wonderful."
    },
    {
      "id": 34,
      "translated": "And here are the pre-trained and post-trained versions"
    },
    {
      "id": 35,
      "translated": "featuring everyone who watched over and supported Ena."
    },
    {
      "id": 36,
      "translated": "Kanade is a creator herself,"
    },
    {
      "id": 37,
      "translated": "so even though their genres are different, she understands Ena's feelings. And KAITO..."
    },
    {
      "id": 38,
      "translated": "Yeah, KAITO gave Ena so many important words of advice."
    },
