response_parts.content:
{
  "response": [
    {
      "id": 0,
      "translated": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "translated": "Man, it really is a great story."
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "translated": "Ena is so loved."
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "translated": "I'm so grateful we got such a wonderful story."
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "translated": "With that said, I'd like to talk about the music after we watch the 3DMV that was written specifically for this event."
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "translated": "Please, take a look."
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "translated": "Breathing inside a borrowed life, in a body that can't become anyone."
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "translated": "If I dive deep into the depths, the me from that day..."
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "translated": "is still smiling."
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "translated": "Looking back, there were certainly fragments of dreams sprouting in my chest."
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "translated": "Pressed down by the weight of strings, they eventually turned into hatred."
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "translated": "There's no use in trying to stroke the past."
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "translated": "This small, gentle light... my belief still won't reach."
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "translated": "Even so, I want to draw more of the future with these hands on the white scenery before me."
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "translated": "Even if the past isn't beautiful, I'll be myself."
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "translated": "I just want to draw..."
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "translated": "this world that reflects in my eyes."
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "translated": "And we're back. Sorry about that."
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "translated": "My screen just popped up there."
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "translated": "That was the 3DMV for the song Chouchou-P wrote for this event, titled \"The Name of Your Drawing.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "translated": "Wait, I got mixed up. That was the 3DMV for \"The Name of Your Drawing.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "translated": "Uh..."
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "translated": "Should I do this first? Oh, it's fine."
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "translated": "For a second, I thought my own notes were Chouchou-P's comments."
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "translated": "I was like, \"Wait, what?\""
    },
    {
      "id": 25,
      "translated": "But I was wrong."
    },
    {
      "id": 26,
      "translated": "Let me read the notes I sent to the staff beforehand."
    },
    {
      "id": 27,
      "translated": "Here they are."
    },
    {
      "id": 28,
      "translated": "\"Just listening to it makes me feel Ena's journey, and it brings me to tears.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 29,
      "translated": "\"The title contains her name, and I felt it was truly a song written for Ena.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 30,
      "translated": "\"I sang it with her determination to turn regret and pain into strength, and with the positive feelings she found.\" That's what past-me emailed to the staff."
    },
    {
      "id": 31,
      "translated": "Chouchou-P's actual comments were introduced on the ProSeka News Station and such."
    },
    {
      "id": 32,
      "translated": "They should be on Twitter—I mean, X—as well, so please check them out."
    },
    {
      "id": 33,
      "translated": "But yeah, those were the feelings I put into the song."
    },
    {
      "id": 34,
      "translated": "Well..."
    },
    {
      "id": 35,
      "translated": "There are lyrics that feel like she's looking back at the past."
    },
    {
      "id": 36,
      "translated": "But it's like the current Ena is the one doing the reflecting."
    },
    {
      "id": 37,
      "translated": "I'm sure Ena has regrets, for sure."
    },
    {
      "id": 38,
      "translated": "But I think she's a girl who understands that those regrets made her who she is today."
    },
    {
      "id": 39,
      "translated": "So even for the phrases about the past, I didn't want to sing them with the pure agony of the old Ena. I sang with my own sense of resolve."
    },
    {
      "id": 40,
      "translated": "Like I said during the story part, I tried to include that sense of relief and the brightness of finally understanding."
    },
    {
      "id": 41,
      "translated": "But this isn't the goal; it's a new start."
    },
    {
      "id": 42,
      "translated": "I was very conscious of capturing that middle-ground feeling while singing."
    },
    {
      "id": 43,
      "translated": "So rather than a huge explosion of emotion, it's more like quietly stirring up words within myself to cheer myself on."
    },
    {
      "id": 44,
      "translated": "Like patting my own chest and saying, \"Let's do this.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 45,
      "translated": "I sang it with that image of self-encouragement in mind."
    },
    {
      "id": 46,
      "translated": "I just end up crying, though."
    },
    {
      "id": 47,
      "translated": "I've already heard the full version, you see."
    },
    {
      "id": 48,
      "translated": "Since I'm the one who sang it."
    },
    {
      "id": 49,
      "translated": "I'm sorry."
    },
    {
      "id": 50,
      "translated": "I just can't help but cry."
    },
    {
      "id": 51,
      "translated": "It's no good."
    },
    {
      "id": 52,
      "translated": "Both this story and the song just make me tear up."
    },
    {
      "id": 53,
      "translated": "What am I going to do? What should we do?"
    },
    {
      "id": 54,
      "translated": "I thought I wouldn't cry this time, either during the talk or the story..."
    },
    {
      "id": 55,
      "translated": "But I did anyway."
    },
    {
      "id": 56,
      "translated": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "id": 57,
      "translated": "To those of you who felt a bit jealous that I've heard the full version, don't worry."
    },
    {
      "id": 58,
      "translated": "The 2DMV for this new song, \"The Name of Your Drawing,\" will be uploaded to the official ProSeka YouTube channel at 10:15 PM."
    },
    {
      "id": 59,
      "translated": "Please check that out along with the 3DMV."
    },
    {
      "id": 60,
      "translated": "If it's like the previous 2DMVs, that means you'll be able to hear the full version too, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 61,
      "translated": "I haven't even seen the 2DMV myself yet."
    },
    {
      "id": 62,
      "translated": "Now, to give some belated thoughts on the 3DMV... I recorded the full song, so I knew how the parts were split."
    },
    {
      "id": 63,
      "translated": "I knew which parts would be Ena's."
    },
    {
      "id": 64,
      "translated": "The song starts with the other three members of Niigo in order."
    },
    {
      "id": 65,
      "translated": "So in the 3DMV inside my head—my imaginary 3DMV—it didn't start with Ena."
    },
    {
      "id": 66,
      "translated": "I was wondering how it would actually begin."
    },
    {
      "id": 67,
      "translated": "Would all four or five of them appear at once?"
    },
    {
      "id": 68,
      "translated": "Or would it start with Mizuki, who has the first line? But then I saw Ena was on screen the whole time."
    },
    {
      "id": 69,
      "translated": "Of course, I'm always happy when other characters get a lot of screen time for their fans, too."
    },
    {
      "id": 70,
      "translated": "But this MV put such a huge spotlight on Ena, and it matched the story so perfectly. It really felt like it was capturing Ena's way of life."
    },
    {
      "id": 71,
      "translated": "As her voice actress, that made me so incredibly happy."
    },
    {
      "id": 72,
      "translated": "It's always the case, but the songs for Ena's stories always feel like the location is gradually moving closer to the surface."
    },
    {
      "id": 73,
      "translated": "Well, that's just my own geeky analysis."
    },
    {
      "id": 74,
      "translated": "But things like that make me happy too."
    },
    {
      "id": 75,
      "translated": "I've only seen it a few times myself, so I want to sit down and watch it properly."
    },
